quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  64,11,"No calamity befalls except with Allah’s permission. Whoever believes in Allah, He will guide his heart. And Allah is All-Knowing of everything"
  64,12,"Obey Allah and obey the Messenger, but if you turn away, then the duty of Our Messenger is only to convey the message clearly"
  64,13,"Allah, none has the right to be worshiped except Him. So in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  64,14,"O you who believe, indeed, among your wives and your children are some who are enemies to you, so beware of them. But if you pardon and overlook, and forgive, then Allah is indeed All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  64,15,"Your wealth and your children are but a trial, and with Allah is a great reward"
  64,16,"So fear Allah as much as you can, listen and obey, and spend in charity; that is better for your souls. Whoever is protected from the stinginess of his soul, it is they who are successful"
  64,17,"If you lend Allah a goodly loan, He will multiply it for you and forgive you, for Allah is Most Appreciative, Most Forbearing"
  64,18,"Knower of the unseen and the seen, the All-Mighty, the All-Wise"